hopobject.body: I saw your advert in the paper street king energy drink uk Yet that's the standard price of business in baseball, where the contract structure all but ensures players enter free agency for the first time when they are at or just past their peaks. Teams vying for the best free agents routinely shell out bloated contracts that, in their closing years, are nothing less than absurd. Just look at the Yankees' debacle with Alex Rodriguez.
